The question asks for Catherine of Pomerania, Countess Palatine of Neumarkt's father-in-law. Catherine of Pomerania was married to Frederick I, Elector of Saxony. I need to find out who Frederick I's father was, as he would be Catherine's father-in-law. Catherine of Pomerania father-in-law identity

Catherine of Pomerania was the wife of Frederick I, Elector of Saxony, and her father-in-law was Rupert, King of Germany.

 The information clearly states that Frederick I, Elector of Saxony, whose wife was Catherine of Pomerania, had Rupert, King of Germany, as his father. Rupert, King of Germany, would be Catherine of Pomerania's father-in-law. Rupert, King of Germany
